  <diagram id="6PNaNdBfEBethFd9qb7F" name="CI Pipeline">
    <mxGraphModel dx="868" dy="1235" grid="1" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="850" pageHeight="1100" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />
        <mxCell id="-RGs64-fcUYjUq_6nOhu-1" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Pipeline Overview&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;The CI Pipeline for the Infrastructure Repo enables changes to the infrastructure baseline from lesser privileged environments and without any contact with the authentication layer. The pipeline triggers on commits to the main branch or via manual triggers. On commit to main, the pipeline will automatically identify files that were changed and attempt to map those files to changes that can be executed automatically: for example, adding/remove static dns records, changing the port configuration on a switch, or managing VM specifications. When triggered manually, users can specify any combination of playbook and tag to execute. The result increments the Build or Revision version and creates a new release, which includes the details necessary to implement the change.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Deployment Executor, hosted on the Management Pi, queries GitLab for releases with changes to implement, claims them, and executes them, delivering the details back to the Release for state tracking and to support troubleshooting.&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="230" width="610" x="20" y="20" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="-RGs64-fcUYjUq_6nOhu-2" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=none;html=1;rounded=0;entryX=0.62;entryY=1.001;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;entryPerimeter=0;" value="">
